\section{Example of |fibo| function}

The function |fibo()| is recursive:

\begin{ffcode}
int fibo(int n) {
  if (n < 2) {
    return n; |$\label{ln:ret}$|
  }
  return fibo(n - 1) + fibo(n - 2);
}
\end{ffcode}

The line~\ref{ln:ret} terminates it.

